      "content": "You're right, clinic wait times in Vancouver can be a bit of a hassle, but if you're not experiencing severe pain, inability to bear weight, or significant instability, it's likely just a sprain. Ibuprofen should help with the pain and inflammation. Ice the ankle for 20 minutes every 2-3 hours while awake, and keep it elevated when you're sitting or lying down. It sounds like you're on the right track. Just keep an eye on it, and if anything changes for the worse, don't hesitate to seek medical attention. But for now, rest, ice, and ibuprofen should do the trick. Take care and get well soon!",
