    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I apologize for the oversight. Your inability to bear weight is a significant symptom, and it's a good indicator that you might be dealing with more than a simple sprain. However, since you're already icing and taking ibuprofen, you're doing the right things to manage the pain and swelling. If you can still bear some weight, even if it's uncomfortable, then it's likely still a sprain. But if you can't bear any weight, it could be a more severe sprain or even a fracture. In that case, I would still recommend seeing a doctor sooner rather than later, but if you must wait, keep monitoring your symptoms closely. If the pain worsens or you can't bear weight, then it's time to see a doctor. But for now, continue with the RICE method and ibuprofen, and try to stay off your ankle as much as possible. If you feel confident that you can bear some weight, then you might just need to take it easy and wait a few days before deciding to see a doctor. But if you're in doubt, err on the side of caution and consult with a medical professional. Your health is paramount, and a little extra caution now could save you from complications later.",
